      • uploadTo

        public static <Tin> Function<Tin,java.lang.Void> uploadTo(java.lang.String filePath,
                                                          boolean append)
        Upload an object to Dropbox, the output file will be at `filePath`. If there is a file already at the `filePath`, the item will be appended to the file. This operator requires Dropbox configured (see https://privacystreams.github.io/pages/enable_accessibility.html). This provider requires `Manifest.permission.INTERNET` permission.
        Type Parameters:
        Tin - the type of input object
        Parameters:
        filePath - the output file path
        Returns:
        the function

      • uploadTo

        public static <Tin> Function<Tin,java.lang.Void> uploadTo(Function<Tin,java.lang.String> filePathGenerator,
                                                          boolean append)
        Upload an object to Dropbox, the output file path will be generated with a function. If file already exists and `append` is true, the object will be appended to the file; If `append` is false, the object will overwrite the existing file. This operator requires Dropbox configured (see https://privacystreams.github.io/pages/enable_accessibility.html). This provider requires `Manifest.permission.INTERNET` permission.
        Type Parameters:
        Tin - the type of input object
        Parameters:
        filePathGenerator - the function to generate the output file path each time
        Returns:
        the function
